# The build context is the repo root. The three top-level Dockerfiles
# (Dockerfile, Dockerfile.musl, Dockerfile.windows) only COPY Cargo.toml,
# Cargo.lock and crates/; tests/e2e/Dockerfile additionally COPYs
# tests/e2e/entrypoint.sh. Allow-list exactly those so the giant siblings —
# target/ (~59G), xet-data/ (~1G), dist/, gitea/, xet-core/, .git/ — never get
# tarred into the context. Add a line here if a Dockerfile starts needing
# another path.
*
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!crates

# Re-include only tests/e2e/entrypoint.sh (the e2e image's entrypoint), not the
# rest of tests/. The nested un-ignore/re-ignore dance is required because a
# file can't be re-included while a parent dir stays excluded.
!tests
tests/*
!tests/e2e
tests/e2e/*
!tests/e2e/entrypoint.sh

# Defensive: never ship a stray build dir that happens to live inside a crate.
crates/**/target/
